# Adding a GitHub repository to MoJ SonarCloud

The Ministry of Justice has a SonarCloud Organisation which Operations Engineering has recently taking ownership of.

This document shares as an internal runbook for Operations Engineering members on how to add a GitHub repository to SonarCloud so that users can use it.

## Prerequisites

* The repository being added *must* be a public repository
* GitHub MoJ Org Admin

## Process

1. Navigate to the [SonarCloud MoJ GitHub App](https://github.com/organizations/ministryofjustice/settings/installations/16911235)
2. Press the "Select repositories" dropdown in the Repository access section
3. Select the repository you wish to add to SonarCloud
4. Press "Save"
5. Navigate to [SonarCloud](https://sonarcloud.io/projects)
6. Log in with GitHub SSO if not already
7. Press the "+"" sign at the top left of the screen
8. Press "Analyze new project"
9. Select the repository you wish to add to SonarCloud
10. Press "Set Up" on the right hand side of the screen

